    [userId] => 42
    [postTitle] => As part of setting up Facebook Login in our app, we need to register a key hash in the Facebook Developer Console. This allows Facebook to verify that our app is legitimate when a user tries to log in.

For testing and development, please add the following key hash under the Development section (we will add the Production one later when publishing to Play Store).

Steps for you to follow:
Go to Facebook Developers Dashboard and log in with your account.

Select our app (App ID: 514510305075906).

In the left menu, go to Facebook Login → Settings.

Scroll down to the Key Hashes section.

In the Development Key Hashes box, paste this value:

eYwm97DahFPA276w9qwP0T6onPU=
Leave the Release Key Hashes empty for now (we will provide this later when we prepare the production build).

Click Save Changes at the bottom.



Why this is needed:
Facebook checks the app’s signing certificate against these hashes.

Without it, login attempts will fail with an “Invalid key hash” error.

The development key hash ensures login works while we test and debug the app on our devices.

Once we are ready to release the app to the Play Store, I will provide you with the production key hash, and you’ll need to add it in the Release Key Hashes box.
    [postType] => Text
)
